##An engineer at Vulcan Mountain Hospital gives an oral statement after completion

WECHAT china30s

Feature description, a platform that encourages you to write about your life. Founded in March 2011, it has a sandwich writing school and a media platform, China Sandwich, at the same time, we are committed to applying the story to cross-border product design, urban culture excavation, exhibition fair, space creation and other three-dimensional field.

Today, the Vulcan Mountain Hospital is officially delivered. The 1,000 bed hospital was built in Wuhan in nine days, following the model of Beijing's Xiaotangshan Hospital during SARS, which caters for COVID-19 pneumonia patients. With hospital beds in short supply, it is not clear how effective or how much relief there will be from the expectations placed on Vulcan and thor.

On the evening of February 1, we reached out to an engineer involved in the Vulcan Mountain Hospital project, who had returned to his home in Wuhan, where he was living in isolation. He told us how he had been feeling these days.

Interview | two dimensional sauce
Dictation | Ye Qiu

"You can go if you want,
Just protect yourself."

On the 26th of the 12th month, when the news of the epidemic became grim, I joked with my wife that Wuhan might have to have a "little Tangshan" as well. Because our unit is the leading enterprise in Wuhan.

The day before New Year's Eve, we got the official news. The leader asked in the group, how many people are in Wuhan? Count again, pull the group, told us: now to build Wuhan "Xiaotangshan" , the need for brothers on top.

One of the brothers said, "if there's a fight, we'll be back, " and they all said it in unison. Yes, "if there is a war, recall, war will be won. " We are fighting a war with no retreat.

When I got the message, I was at home watching a movie with my two children and enjoying a rare family time together. The company had just finished its first day of meetings and holidays. I didn't hesitate to send a message in the group, but how do I tell my family? I hesitated. I told my wife at dinner that I had something to do with the project, and I'm going tomorrow. Thought I'd check in, maybe come back every day. But the daughter-in-law knew me too well, got suspicious, kept asking me until midnight, asked me what I want to do. I had to hand her my phone.

I know. She's GonNa be so worried if we go out there right now. But when she saw it, she said nothing. After a while, she said, "you can go if you want. Just protect yourself. "

In fact, we have received some information, know the situation is very serious, in the hospital work friends called US early, said someone passed, we wear a mask, pay attention.

When the COVID-19 first reported the story, a friend who was a doctor sent me a video of an elderly father sitting on his deathbed, his wife standing around crying, in fact, it is not going to be able to say, who can save us. My friend sent me this video to let me see the real situation, remind us and the family elders to do more work, can not go out. The video actually touched me a lot, especially the longing for life and the despair of reality in the eyes of two old people. After I saw it, I felt so bad, I told my wife I was going to take a shower, and then I cried for a while in the water. At that time I said to myself to do something, not to go to the South Hospital to do a volunteer help, can contribute as much as possible. I didn't know we were going to another war.

Actually, I was a little scared the night before I decided to go to Vulcan Mountain. After Zhong came to Wuhan, the number of confirmed cases and suspected cases rose every day, making it difficult to get a bed in every hospital in Wuhan. But here is Wuhan, here is my home, a birth I bring up I see I grow up place, I primary school, Middle School, university until marriage have children in Wuhan.

Even after work with the unit to go north and south, all over half of China, finally want to be in Wuhan, would rather cut pay or do not promote, just want to stay in Wuhan. Only in Wuhan can there be that feeling of home, not out of the time did not feel, really out, the Ordinary Heroes is a line, I want to go back to Wuhan.

On the day of the siege, at around 10 p.m. the night before, I asked my daughter-in-law if she wanted to go back to her hometown of Suizhou. At that time the idea is that daughter-in-law home has a more than 300 flat courtyard, even if not go out two children in the past can also be happy to play for a while, later Wuhan long-term do not go out, two children at home very depressed. But on second thought, even if out, but also stay at home, this time, Wuhan out of the certainly not welcome. Moreover, the medical conditions in Wuhan are better than those in the surrounding areas. Moreover, in the early days, Wuhan did not pay enough attention, and the surrounding areas did not pay enough attention. It is hard to say what the situation of the epidemic in the later period was. It was better to stay at home and not go out.

My two children, a five-year-old son and a seven-year-old daughter, still don't quite understand it. I showed them some videos and said that many people outside are sick now. This disease is very contagious. We should wash our hands and wear masks frequently. Before I left, I told them, "Daddy's going off to war tomorrow. " My son was happy, and boys always had a strange hunger for war. My daughter was a little scared and told me to be careful.

I told the leaders to report the next morning, before dawn at about 5:00, from my home to drive about 50 kilometers. When I went out, I took nothing with me, because I thought there was a simple wash bag and some change of clothes in the car. I thought I might be able to go home every day, maybe two or three days at the most, but then I realized I couldn't.

Had A few days where I forgot to check in with my family

By the time we arrived at the construction site, there were already more than 30 management personnel from our company. Some excavators were working at the site, about 20 more.

I am mainly responsible for the deployment of containers, sub-loading, on the one hand contact manufacturers, from all over, on the one hand with the design docking. A few days ago when the container did not work mainly on the site to help coordinate the scene, the back involved in the container assembly, to be assembled outside, and then sent. So you need to keep running back and forth, every day back and forth to go through nearly ten times. There are a lot of road in the vicinity of the Vulcan Mountain, some are to measure body temperature, some are to check the pass, Management Card.

The average number of steps per day should be over 30,000. The phone becomes a burden, and every time the phone rings, the Scalp Tingles, because it may mean new changes, and a lot of previous work is useless.

Just past, every day a lot of friends call to ask me, is not in the Vulcan Mountain, there is how the situation, and want to see the scene photos. Many are very boring, before and after there are hundreds of such calls, all kinds of friends and relatives and classmates to ask. I understand your curiosity about this place, but I'm too busy to share it with you.

Everyone's work time said is day night double shift, in fact, did not do so, too tired to go back to rest, woke up the first time back to the scene. I usually work till 11:00 or 12:00 at night, and I usually get up at 5:00 or 6:00 in the morning to go. New Year's Eve is the busiest day, the first day at seven o'clock to the construction site, the next day lunch before returning to the project to rest. I don't really have time to notice when it's New Year's Eve or whatever. Sometimes in the construction site to see the new colleagues, we call each other to say a "happy New Year" , more is a polite greeting, this time, no one will be in the mood for New Year.

I live in the project department of the surrounding project, but because of the more people, the back to the brothers arranged to a nearby hotel. We set up a few large tents on the site as our temporary supply point and checkpoint, to the meal point we go there to pick up lunch boxes, usually three or four dishes. Take it, in the edge of a random place to eat, we are conscious to maintain a certain distance.

We're on a construction site, and all we've got is a mask and a hard hat. From the third day, there are special people here in the tent to hand out masks, recycling masks, three times a day to take body temperature. It is estimated that this disease is still related to the personal immune system. People who usually work more on the spot are in good health. Basically, no one has any problems. Only one or two people caught a cold in the first two days because of the rain during construction, they were quarantined as a precaution.

In addition to the first day of resources have not yet deployed in place, the poor conditions, the conditions behind are quite good, supplies are also relatively sufficient. Here also thanks to many warm-hearted person's contribution, lets us in the logistics procurement aspect pressure to reduce many.

The hospital's under a lot more pressure here than we are. On the 30th day of the Lunar New Year, the hospital ran out of supplies and supplies. A friend of mine in Japan asked me to send some masks to my father, who works in the hospital. The first thing I did on the first day of the Lunar New Year was to rush to the hospital, but I couldn't send them in at all, ask their head nurse to come out and get it but they can't use it, because our standards are so low, they can't use it. My friend's father he's a surgeon at the hospital, and we're short-handed, and I can't get in there without him in the ICU. All the calls were made on his behalf. He said, "you go back to your job, I'll go back to mine. We'll have another drink after this. ".

I don't know what's going on with him, and I don't want to ask. Maybe no news is the best news.

Family members sometimes ask how things are going, take care of yourself and so on. But a few days were totally unrelated, and I was too busy to remember.

In the Vulcan Mountain and at home is a completely different mood, at home before the departure may have panic, fear, tension, and so on, out, what a mess of emotions will not have. All the ups and downs are with some things at work and fluctuations, other things, no time to think.

The other day it was rainy and we were worried about the setting time of the concrete after pouring. Fortunately, the next few days are sunny, weather, temperature is good, to save us a lot of time. Overall, it went pretty well.

The speed of construction, in fact, no surprise, we began to be a particularly tight schedule for the project, in fact, the technical content is not so big. Foreign media praised the "Chinese speed" , in fact, China has been very fast, far faster than they thought, China's construction industry is really strong.

The baby tried to hug me,
I stopped it

When we eat, we look at the news about the epidemic, one is to look at the data, the number of infections, the number of deaths, to see if there are any new rumors.

Some of the news is really funny, such as yesterday's Shuanghuanglian. Actually yesterday I had a little cough, ran to the pharmacy to buy some cough medicine, casually took a few boxes of medicine, there is double Coptis inside. See The news in the evening, I also joked with friends around, I have two boxes of double Coptis, high price, a box of 200. It's fake. It's not working. I don't know where their shame lies in a report from a very large research institute that has no basis whatsoever.

On-line Vulcan Mountain live broadcast is very popular, I was very late to know, is a friend to call me up. The nickname I got was "Emperor Gaozong of Song. " I knew it because a classmate insisted that I send him a picture of the scene, so I took a quick photo and he said it was "Emperor Gaozong of Song. " I don't know what it means, and he explained it to me. Mixed with what little red and blue and so on, I really can not remember, can not imagine this a construction machinery and pet the same name.

Construction site filming

Someone told me that this monitoring thing is very high-tech and so on. In fact, most of our projects will also install monitoring when they are under construction. There will also be data on the temperature, humidity and dust state at that time, which is part of the daily work, it's flat. I think people have this kind of interest should be at home for a long time, if you can go out to play, who would like to see people play in the mud.

Live from the construction site

When the construction did not really have the mood, including that can go home, there is no feeling, only after the job after the exhaustion. This construction task is not difficult, is too tight schedule pressure, to complete the task or more confident.

Really home, see the daughter-in-law, see the children, or feel happy. See Me, the Child Foolishly said "dad finally came back, I miss you" , they want to come over to hug me, I quickly to stop. I was wearing a mask, and I was wearing the same clothes. Throw your clothes in the washing machine, clean them and lock yourself in your room.

I got a really good brother, a cop, he had a fever on the first day of the New Year, and the day before I got back, his wife asked me if I could get immunoglobulins, so I got him some. Now he's in Wuchang Hospital. He's undiagnosed. I had a friend of mine, a doctor, take a look at him. He's basically diagnosed.

Not only is it difficult to diagnose, but it's also difficult for the hospital to take you in, because it's full. It's a really hard bed to get.

I went home today, and I want to be isolated, at least for a week. All the family members who ate it. Throat a little inflammation, should be the Pharyngitis, go before there is Pharyngitis, more than a month, and now a little cough.

At home, occasionally can wear a mask to the balcony, see more than a dozen Goldfish, there are several pots of orchids, my daughter-in-law's hometown is the hometown of orchids. Children like small animals, previously had a hamster, blue cat, but children often play with small animals were scratched, on the Goldfish, safety first. Now with Nissu, Phuc Tho, Thai Lion, Cat Lion, I came back to see the cat lion is shaking his tail Gnawing Moss, watching them in the water carefree swim to and fro, it is very quiet. Let's hope we all survive this disaster.

Even after work with the unit to go north and south, all over half of China, finally want to be in Wuhan, would rather cut pay or do not promote, just want to stay in Wuhan. Only in Wuhan can there be that feeling of home, not out of the time did not feel, really out, the Ordinary Heroes is a line, I want to go back to Wuhan.

On the day of the siege, at around 10 p.m. the night before, I asked my daughter-in-law if she wanted to go back to her hometown of Suizhou. At that time the idea is that daughter-in-law home has a more than 300 flat courtyard, even if not go out two children in the past can also be happy to play for a while, later Wuhan long-term do not go out, two children at home very depressed. But on second thought, even if out, but also stay at home, this time, Wuhan out of the certainly not welcome. Moreover, the medical conditions in Wuhan are better than those in the surrounding areas. Moreover, in the early days, Wuhan did not pay enough attention, and the surrounding areas did not pay enough attention. It is hard to say what the situation of the epidemic in the later period was. It was better to stay at home and not go out.

My two children, a five-year-old son and a seven-year-old daughter, still don't quite understand it. I showed them some videos and said that many people outside are sick now. This disease is very contagious. We should wash our hands and wear masks frequently. Before I left, I told them, "Daddy's going off to war tomorrow. " My son was happy, and boys always had a strange hunger for war. My daughter was a little scared and told me to be careful.

I told the leaders to report the next morning, before dawn at about 5:00, from my home to drive about 50 kilometers. When I went out, I took nothing with me, because I thought there was a simple wash bag and some change of clothes in the car. I thought I might be able to go home every day, maybe two or three days at the most, but then I realized I couldn't.

On the 26th of the 12th month, when the news of the epidemic became grim, I joked with my wife that Wuhan might have to have a "little Tangshan" as well. Because our unit is the leading enterprise in Wuhan.

The day before New Year's Eve, we got the official news. The leader asked in the group, how many people are in Wuhan? Count again, pull the group, told us: now to build Wuhan "Xiaotangshan" , the need for brothers on top.

One of the brothers said, "if there's a fight, we'll be back, " and they all said it in unison. Yes, "if there is a war, recall, war will be won. " We are fighting a war with no retreat.

When I got the message, I was at home watching a movie with my two children and enjoying a rare family time together. The company had just finished its first day of meetings and holidays. I didn't hesitate to send a message in the group, but how do I tell my family? I hesitated. I told my wife at dinner that I had something to do with the project, and I'm going tomorrow. Thought I'd check in, maybe come back every day. But the daughter-in-law knew me too well, got suspicious, kept asking me until midnight, asked me what I want to do. I had to hand her my phone.

I know. She's GonNa be so worried if we go out there right now. But when she saw it, she said nothing. After a while, she said, "you can go if you want. Just protect yourself. "

In fact, we have received some information, know the situation is very serious, in the hospital work friends called US early, said someone passed, we wear a mask, pay attention.

When the COVID-19 first reported the story, a friend who was a doctor sent me a video of an elderly father sitting on his deathbed, his wife standing around crying, in fact, it is not going to be able to say, who can save us. My friend sent me this video to let me see the real situation, remind us and the family elders to do more work, can not go out. The video actually touched me a lot, especially the longing for life and the despair of reality in the eyes of two old people. After I saw it, I felt so bad, I told my wife I was going to take a shower, and then I cried for a while in the water. At that time I said to myself to do something, not to go to the South Hospital to do a volunteer help, can contribute as much as possible. I didn't know we were going to another war.

Actually, I was a little scared the night before I decided to go to Vulcan Mountain. Had A few days where I forgot to check in with my family

By the time we arrived at the construction site, there were already more than 30 management personnel from our company. Some excavators were working at the site, about 20 more.

I am mainly responsible for the deployment of containers, sub-loading, on the one hand contact manufacturers, from all over, on the one hand with the design docking. A few days ago when the container did not work mainly on the site to help coordinate the scene, the back involved in the container assembly, to be assembled outside, and then sent. So you need to keep running back and forth, every day back and forth to go through nearly ten times. There are a lot of road in the vicinity of the Vulcan Mountain, some are to measure body temperature, some are to check the pass, Management Card.

The average number of steps per day should be over 30,000. The phone becomes a burden, and every time the phone rings, the Scalp Tingles, because it may mean new changes, and a lot of previous work is useless.

Just past, every day a lot of friends call to ask me, is not in the Vulcan Mountain, there is how the situation, and want to see the scene photos. Many are very boring, before and after there are hundreds of such calls, all kinds of friends and relatives and classmates to ask. I understand your curiosity about this place, but I'm too busy to share it with you.

Everyone's work time said is day night double shift, in fact, did not do so, too tired to go back to rest, woke up the first time back to the scene. I usually work till 11:00 or 12:00 at night, and I usually get up at 5:00 or 6:00 in the morning to go. New Year's Eve is the busiest day, the first day at seven o'clock to the construction site, the next day lunch before returning to the project to rest. I don't really have time to notice when it's New Year's Eve or whatever. Sometimes in the construction site to see the new colleagues, we call each other to say a "happy New Year" , more is a polite greeting, this time, no one will be in the mood for New Year.

I live in the project department of the surrounding project, but because of the more people, the back to the brothers arranged to a nearby hotel. We set up a few large tents on the site as our temporary supply point and checkpoint, to the meal point we go there to pick up lunch boxes, usually three or four dishes. Take it, in the edge of a random place to eat, we are conscious to maintain a certain distance.

We're on a construction site, and all we've got is a mask and a hard hat. From the third day, there are special people here in the tent to hand out masks, recycling masks, three times a day to take body temperature. It is estimated that this disease is still related to the personal immune system. People who usually work more on the spot are in good health. Basically, no one has any problems. Only one or two people caught a cold in the first two days because of the rain during construction, they were quarantined as a precaution.

In addition to the first day of resources have not yet deployed in place, the poor conditions, the conditions behind are quite good, supplies are also relatively sufficient. Here also thanks to many warm-hearted person's contribution, lets us in the logistics procurement aspect pressure to reduce many.

The hospital's under a lot more pressure here than we are. On the 30th day of the Lunar New Year, the hospital ran out of supplies and supplies. A friend of mine in Japan asked me to send some masks to my father, who works in the hospital. The first thing I did on the first day of the Lunar New Year was to rush to the hospital, but I couldn't send them in at all, ask their head nurse to come out and get it but they can't use it, because our standards are so low, they can't use it. My friend's father he's a surgeon at the hospital, and we're short-handed, and I can't get in there without him in the ICU. All the calls were made on his behalf. He said, "you go back to your job, I'll go back to mine. We'll have another drink after this. ".

I don't know what's going on with him, and I don't want to ask. Maybe no news is the best news.

Family members sometimes ask how things are going, take care of yourself and so on. But a few days were totally unrelated, and I was too busy to remember.

In the Vulcan Mountain and at home is a completely different mood, at home before the departure may have panic, fear, tension, and so on, out, what a mess of emotions will not have. All the ups and downs are with some things at work and fluctuations, other things, no time to think.

The other day it was rainy and we were worried about the setting time of the concrete after pouring. Fortunately, the next few days are sunny, weather, temperature is good, to save us a lot of time. Overall, it went pretty well.

The speed of construction, in fact, no surprise, we began to be a particularly tight schedule for the project, in fact, the technical content is not so big. Foreign media praised the "Chinese speed" , in fact, China has been very fast, far faster than they thought, China's construction industry is really strong.
